               <msContents>
                  <summary>Leaf of a papyrus codex with a magical handbook from Egypt. Has instructions for various spells including a love-charm that details the preparation of a potion and mentions Aphrodite, a charm to force silence on a person, a love charm or binding spell containing magical symbols, and a hymn to the sun (Helios) to accompany any request. The hymn identifies the sun with among other things, Harpokrates, Yahweh, Abrasax, Hephaistos and Mithras</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 14.8 x 10.2 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">54 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto; written across the fibers on the verso</note>
                     <note type="general">Margin of 1 cm. on the recto; left margin of 1 cm. on the verso</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 729 was formerly P.Duk.inv. LK76 2</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
